61    /**
62    * Tests that the given JavaScript code has a @deprecated marker
63    * somewhere in it which raises an error. Also tests that the
64    * deprecated marker works with a message. The JavaScript should
65    * have a JsDoc of the form "@deprecated %s\n".
66    *
67    * @param js The JavaScript code to parse and test.
68    * @param reason A simple deprecation reason string, used for testing
69    * the addition of a deprecation reason to the @deprecated tag.
70    * @param error The deprecation error expected when no reason is given.
71    * @param errorWithMessage The deprecation error expected when a reason
72    * message is given.
73    */
 
100% Uncovered Elements: 0 (2) Complexity: 1 Complexity Density: 0.5

79  66 test(String.format(js, ""), null, error);
80   
81    // Test with a reason.
82  66 test(String.format(js, reason), null, errorWithMessage, null, reason);
83    }
